<h2><b>Features</b></h2>

<p style="color:black;font-size:24px!important;">
    The TruckApp has the following features:
    <ul style="color: black;font-size: 24px !important;">
        <li>
            <b>TypeAhead</b> - the feature allows the user to see the list of options to chose from. TypeAhead is available for
            Customer's name and address fiealds as well as for the Confirmation number field on the load confirmation page.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>Autocompletion</b> - if the user knows the customer's id in the database, he can enter it in the Customer's id field on the
            load confirmation form page and the TruckApp will autocomplete all other required fields for this customer.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>AutoEditing</b> - all the input fields in the TruckApp edit the data keyed by the user
            (convert the input into the uppercase, delete the forbidden characters,
            delete spaces in the beginning and in the end, delete the redundant spaces). The number input fields delete all characters
            and leave only numbers. The time and date input fields autocomplete the input. If the user enters one or two
            digits and presses "Enter", the TruckApp will deem the digits to be the day of the current month and year.
            If the user enters three or four digits, the application will complete them using the current year.
            When user would like to enter the whole date, he can enter all ten digits.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>Validation</b> - the TruckApp validates the user's entry. For example, the application won't allow the user to save the
            confirmation load if even one of the mandatory fields is empty. Also, special validation rules apply to such input fields as:
            <br /> - date (for example, the application will notify the user that the date that he entered has already passed etc.),
            <br /> - rate (for example, the application will notify the user if the user has entered the rate larger than $10,000 etc.),
            <br /> - the attached files are required to be "pdf" files with the maximum size of 3Mb,
            <br /> - and so on.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>Duplicate protection</b> - the TruckApp won't allow the user to save two load confirmations with the similar confirmation
            number to prevent duplicates. When the user enters the confirmation number TypeAhead will show him the duplicate confirmation
            numbers that are already have been keyed into the system. If the user try to enter duplicate, the TruckApp will show notification
            with the possible duplicate details.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>DataTables</b> - almost all tables in the TruckApp have sorting and searching. The TruckApp does the search on all columns
            at once. Almost all tables are interactive. The user can click on the certain row or a button to perform the corresponding action.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>Smart Entry</b> - the user won't be allowed to add a note, attach a file, add a stop, go to the "leg page" or see 
            the "Actions" performed on the load confirmation before the load confirmation has been actually created 
            (the "Save" button was pressed).
        </li>
    </ul>
</p>


